abstract="Program transformation by supercompilation is summarized. The current state of work on supercompilation is illustrated by several examples of successful transformation. In the process of work it became clear that many different supercompilers can be written by using various techniques in their basic modules. A formal language to describe these techniques is needed. An outline of such a language, SCPL, for the top level of control in a supercompiler is given.",
